Dress by @dannijo

node.text:
Cocktail hour brought to you by #DramaQueens @dramaqueensoth featuring our friends #JaneWalker @johnniewalker @dradamshob @combierusa 
Dress by @saylorny 
•
#cocktailhour #roseysour #bartending #whiskylover #whiskeysour #cocktails #happyhour #drinks
•
Non-Alch alternative:
Use a whiskey sub like Kentucky Spiritless, mix with a rose flavored syrup like @monin_usa or @torani and alcohol free bitters like @dramapothecary or @feebrothersbitters. If you don’t have access to those bitters. You can make your own concoction in a small pot with black tea, hazelnut, vanilla, ginger & citrus peel boiled down until very strong. Add .5 tsp to the drink mix. 🌱 🍊

node.text:
Working on a little country tune.

No one but you, no one- not anybody- is gonna be on my my mind. I ain’t the leaving kind. No on but you, no one could keep me coming back for the rest of my life. I ain’t the leaving kind. 

If you got one heart, I got two arms and I will hold you through the cold and dark. And I will say to you “my love is always true, even when it’s hard to find. Darling, I ain’t the leaving kind” 🎶 💋

node.text:
A moment from the road. @highlineballroom My east coast concert tour joined by @binxlefae and @benzelico 
I see Sundays on a big couch in a big house, with a record player singing through the rooms. I see me in some old sundress making breakfast while you paint or tear apart something you’ve been rewriting every afternoon. Am i crazy? Or is this happening to you too? I see long drives on the coast and paper bags with little lunches as i watch you in the waves or read a while. And we’re fighting on occasion over all the usual suspects, yes, but mostly we just know each other too damn well to lose. Is it just me? Or is this me and you? I’m sure you’ve had your share of all the other girls out there and I’m aware that we’re just shaking hands. And I’ve got a lot to lose so I don’t want to speak too soon but I guess we’ve both been runnin’ through the sand. Can we be alone? Can you take me home? I need just a minute please, apparently I cannot speak. I never feel so many things. You’ll have to be forgiving. Babe, I’m shoddy at the games, I push harder than I mean.  I really only know one thing- we should be together. I don’t want anybody else, just you. I don’t want anybody else, just you. I don’t want anybody else, just you... I see Sundays on a big couch in a big house, with a record player singing through the rooms. I see me in some old sundress making breakfast while you paint any afternoon. Am i crazy? Or is this me and you?

Available now on my new album SNOW ❄️ Link in Bio
•
I wrote this as a quartet for my staged musical version of The Notebook from like 10 years ago.  This song was originally between Lon, Allie and her parents. Well, “never let anything go to waste” I say, so here it is in a duet with my wonderful friend @anthonyevansjr! You may know him from @nbcthevoice or from his broad career as a recording artist (go check out HIS christmas album too!!) and he’s also an author- #UnexpectedPlaces is avail now online and in bookstores. I’m not great at this video/app/phone thing but here’s a little something cute and you can hear the whole song too ❤️
Go buy SNOW! Xoxox

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bethany Joy Lenz on August 15, 2021. May be an image of nature, bridge and body of water.

node.text:
We are so small, but what we believe about how loved we are, in spite of our finite nature, informs every choice we make in life. 
•
Human love is necessary and important, but it’s also fleeting, contractual, conditional… human love feels wonderful, but is the fickle “praise of the praiseworthy” really worth being the thing in which you stake your value & identity if the “praiseworthy” is another person, (or even a job)?
•
What, or Who is truly Praiseworthy? And if that thing or person loves you how would it change you? Not an abstract, general love, but a deep knowing kind of love. The kind of love that sees all your flaws and loves you anyway, that sees all your strengths and cares about helping you use them…
•
I would argue that we seek this kind of love from human partners and wrap our identity into it, yet if we ever lose it — it destroys us 💔
Why not put our value, self worth, self confidence into a love that will never fail? Do you believe it exists? 🦅🪨🕊 #steadylove
